                "name": "Undersized Weapons",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "Although a lamia is Large, its upper torso is the same size as that of a Medium humanoid. As a result, lamias wield weapons as if they were one size category smaller than their actual size."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Wisdom Drain",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su",
                "text": "A lamia drains 1d4 points of Wisdom each time it hits with its melee touch attack (unlike with other kinds of ability drain attacks, a lamia doesn\u2019t regain hit points when it uses its Wisdom drain). Lamias try to use this power early in an encounter to make foes more susceptible to <i>charm monster </i>and <i>suggestion</i>."
